  <h1>How do I set up TikTok Events API on Shopify without code?</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    <strong>Use the free TikTok Events API tool by Stack Architect</strong> — it connects your Shopify store to TikTok's Events API server-side in under 10 minutes, no developer access or custom code required. You need only your TikTok Pixel ID and an Events API Access Token from TikTok Business Center.
  </p>

  <div class="meta-row">
    <span>UPDATED: April 2026</span>
    <span>READ TIME: 4 min</span>
    <span>CATEGORY: TikTok Ads</span>
  </div>

  <h2>// What You Need Before You Start</h2>
  <ul class="req-list">
    <li>TikTok Business Center account <span>— free, create at business.tiktok.com</span></li>
    <li>TikTok Pixel created in Events Manager <span>— note the Pixel ID (numeric)</span></li>
    <li>Events API Access Token <span>— generated in Events Manager → Manage → Generate Access Token</span></li>
    <li>Your Shopify store URL <span>— yourstore.myshopify.com</span></li>
  </ul>
  <p>No coding knowledge required. No Shopify app install required. No developer access required.</p>

  <h2>// Setup Steps — Under 10 Minutes</h2>

  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">01</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="step-title">Get your TikTok Events API credentials</div>
        <div class="step-desc">In TikTok Business Center → Events Manager, find your Pixel ID (a long numeric string). Then go to Manage → Generate Access Token and copy the token. These are the only two credentials you need.</div>
        <div class="step-time">⏱ 2–3 minutes</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">02</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="step-title">Open the TikTok Events API tool</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Go to stackarchitect.xyz/tiktok-events-api-shopify. Click "Connect Shopify Store" and authorise via Shopify OAuth — you'll be redirected to your Shopify admin to approve the connection. No app install on Shopify's side.</div>
        <div class="step-time">⏱ 1 minute</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">03</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="step-title">Enter your TikTok credentials</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Paste your Pixel ID and Access Token into the configuration fields. Select which events to send server-side: at minimum, enable Purchase and AddToCart.</div>
        <div class="step-time">⏱ 1 minute</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-num">04</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <div class="step-title">Test with a real order</div>
        <div class="step-desc">Place a test order on your Shopify store (use a 100% discount code). In TikTok Events Manager → Test Events, verify that a Purchase event appears with source "API" within 30 seconds.</div>
        <div class="step-time">⏱ 3–5 minutes</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>// Which Events to Send Server-Side</h2>
  <p>
    Send all events server-side that your TikTok Pixel already fires browser-side. Server-side and browser events run in parallel — TikTok's deduplication logic (using the same <code>event_id</code> from both sources) prevents double-counting.
  </p>

  <div class="events-grid">
    <div class="event-card">
      <div class="event-name">Purchase</div>
      <div class="event-desc">Completed order. Highest priority — recovers the most iOS-blocked conversions.</div>
      <div class="event-priority">★ Critical — enable first</div>
    </div>
    <div class="event-card">
      <div class="event-name">InitiateCheckout</div>
      <div class="event-desc">Customer reaches checkout page. Feeds upper-funnel optimisation signals.</div>
      <div class="event-priority">★ Recommended</div>
    </div>
    <div class="event-card">
      <div class="event-name">AddToCart</div>
      <div class="event-desc">Product added to cart. Improves remarketing audience quality.</div>
      <div class="event-priority">Recommended</div>
    </div>
    <div class="event-card">
      <div class="event-name">ViewContent</div>
      <div class="event-desc">Product page viewed. Useful for top-of-funnel campaigns.</div>
      <div class="event-priority">Optional — higher volume</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="highlight-box">
    <div class="label">TIKTOK PIXEL + EVENTS API — RUN BOTH</div>
    <p style="margin:0; font-size:13px;">Do not remove your TikTok Pixel when setting up the Events API. Running both in parallel gives TikTok more signal to work with. The Pixel captures browser-side events (including ViewContent and AddToCart where server-side overhead isn't needed), while the Events API captures Purchase events server-side where accuracy is critical. Deduplication via event_id prevents double-counting.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>// Why This Matters for TikTok Ads Performance</h2>
  <p>
    TikTok's algorithm optimises ad delivery toward people most likely to convert. If your Purchase events are missing 30–50% of actual conversions due to iOS tracking restrictions, TikTok is training its algorithm on incomplete data — resulting in worse targeting, higher CPAs, and underreported ROAS. Recovering missing Purchase events with server-side tracking gives TikTok a more accurate picture of who converts, which improves campaign performance over time as the algorithm recalibrates.
  </p>

  <!-- FAQ ACCORDION -->
  <div class="faq-section">
    <h2>// Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Will this affect my TikTok Pixel data?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        The TikTok Events API adds server-side events alongside your existing Pixel — it does not replace or modify your Pixel setup. With deduplication active, TikTok Events Manager will show a combined view of browser and server events. You may see total reported conversions increase as previously-blocked iOS events are recovered. This is normal and reflects your actual conversion volume more accurately.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Is there a free tier for TikTok Events API?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        TikTok's Events API itself is completely free. The Stack Architect TikTok Events API tool for Shopify is also permanently free — no subscription, no trial expiry. The only cost is your TikTok ad spend itself, which is unaffected by this setup.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Does TikTok Events API work on Shopify headless or custom storefronts?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        The Stack Architect TikTok Events API tool works with standard Shopify storefronts and Shopify Online Store 2.0. For headless or custom storefront setups, a custom Events API implementation using TikTok's API directly is required. The full technical documentation for the TikTok Events API is available in TikTok's Business Center help docs.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">How long does it take to see results in TikTok Ads?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Server-side events appear in TikTok Events Manager within seconds of firing. Reported conversion improvements in TikTok Ads Manager appear within 24–48 hours as the attribution window recalculates. Campaign performance improvements from better optimisation signals typically emerge over 7–14 days as TikTok's algorithm incorporates the additional conversion data into audience targeting.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

